model Model
	culture: en-US
	defaultPowerBIDataSourceVersion: powerBI_V3
	sourceQueryCulture: en-US
	dataAccessOptions
		legacyRedirects
		returnErrorValuesAsNull

annotation PBI_QueryOrder = ["DirectLake - lh_enercare_demo"]

annotation __PBI_TimeIntelligenceEnabled = 1

annotation PBI_ProTooling = ["DirectLakeOnOneLakeInWeb", "TMDL-Extension", "SLL"]

annotation PBI_AI_Instructions = Enercare is a Canadian home services company providing HVAC maintenance, water heater rentals, Protection Plans (PP), and Ecobee smart thermostat installation in Ontario. Billing systems: ZUORA (recurring), NS (NetSuite), CLARIFY (CRM/field service). PP = Protection Plan throughout this system. MRR = Monthly Recurring Revenue. The contact center handles billing, PP renewal, HVAC service, emergency, new sales, and Ecobee support queues. | FCR = First Contact Resolution (resolved without callback in 5 business days). CSAT = Customer Satisfaction Score (1â€“5 IVR survey, ~22% response rate). AHT = Average Handle Time (talk + hold + wrap seconds). PP_RNW_RATE = Protection Plan Renewal Rate (target 82%). SLA Breach = field technician missed committed service window. WH = Water Heater. HVAC = Heating Ventilation Air Conditioning. MUR = Multi-Unit Residential. FSA = Forward Sortation Area (first 3 chars of postal code). | FCR = First Contact Resolution (resolved without callback in 5 business days). CSAT = Customer Satisfaction Score (1–5 IVR survey, ~22% response rate). AHT = Average Handle Time (talk + hold + wrap seconds). PP_RNW_RATE = Protection Plan Renewal Rate (target 82%). SLA Breach = field technician missed committed service window. WH = Water Heater. HVAC = Heating Ventilation Air Conditioning. MUR = Multi-Unit Residential. FSA = Forward Sortation Area (first 3 chars of postal code). | Five certified call center KPIs: FCR target 78% (warning <72%, critical <65%); CSAT target 4.2/5 (warning <3.8, critical <3.4); PP_RNW_RATE target 82% (warning <75%, critical <68%); AHT target 420s billing queue (warning >480s, critical >540s); SLA_BRCH_RATE target 5% (warning >10%, critical >15%). Only IsCertified=1 KPIs have been approved by Christopher Dingle. Do not present non-certified measures as authoritative business KPIs. | VERIFIED Q&A: Q: what is our FCR -> FCR (First Contact Resolution) measures whether a customer's issue was resolved in a single interaction without a callback within 5 business days. Tar | Q: first contact resolution -> First Contact Resolution Rate is the percentage of inbound interactions that did not generate a follow-up contact within 5 business days. It is our pr | Q: call back rate -> Callback rate is the inverse of FCR. If FCR is 78%, approximately 22% of customers contacted us again within 5 days about the same issue. | Q: how often do customers call back -> FCR tracks this. An FCR below 72% (warning threshold) means more than 28% of customers needed a follow-up contact within 5 business days. | Q: what is our CSAT -> CSAT (Customer Satisfaction Score) is a post-call IVR survey score from 1 to 5 (5 = very satisfied). Only ~22% of customers complete the survey. Targe | Q: what is our CSAT -> CSAT (Customer Satisfaction Score) is a post-call IVR survey score from 1 to 5 (5 = very satisfied). Only ~22% of customers complete the survey. Targe | Q: customer satisfaction -> Customer satisfaction is measured via post-call IVR survey on a 1â€“5 scale. CSAT below 3.5 on a queue indicates a systemic issue, not individual agen | Q: customer satisfaction -> Customer satisfaction is measured via post-call IVR survey on a 1–5 scale. CSAT below 3.5 on a queue indicates a systemic issue, not individual agent | Q: how happy are customers -> Use the CSAT measure, which averages post-call survey responses. Only ~22% of customers respond â€” filter for non-null csat_score for accurate averag | Q: how happy are customers -> Use the CSAT measure, which averages post-call survey responses. Only ~22% of customers respond — filter for non-null csat_score for accurate averages | Q: satisfaction score -> CSAT averages the IVR survey score across interactions. Filter to completed surveys (csat_score IS NOT NULL) when calculating. Target: 4.2 out of 5. | Q: PP renewal rate -> PP Renewal Rate measures how many customers renew their HVAC or water heater Protection Plans. This is the primary retention KPI. Renewal window: 30 d | Q: protection plan renewal -> Protection Plan Renewal Rate = renewed / (renewed + lapsed + cancelled) contracts that reached expiry. Applies to HVAC_PLAN and WH_RENTAL_PLAN product | Q: how many customers renewed -> Use PP_RNW_RATE. Renewals can happen via inbound call, outbound retention call, online portal, or direct mail. Target: 82% renewal rate. | Q: renewal rate -> PP Renewal Rate target is 82%. Customers calling the billing queue before renewal date and not renewing often signals billing confusion â€” cross-refe | Q: renewal rate -> PP Renewal Rate target is 82%. Customers calling the billing queue before renewal date and not renewing often signals billing confusion — cross-refere | Q: contract renewal -> Contract renewal performance is tracked by PP_RNW_RATE. Renewal window: 30 days before to 15 days after the contract end date.

ref table dim_date
ref table dim_equipment
ref table dim_customer
ref table dim_service_account
ref table dim_product
ref table fct_service_request
ref table fct_billing
ref table fct_contract_month
ref table _Measures
ref table dim_cc_agent
ref table dim_cc_billing_adj
ref table fct_cc_interactions
ref table fct_cc_transcript_turns

